solutions.content:
From the problem description we have "a rooted tree is a directed graph such that, there is exactly one node (the root) for which all other nodes are descendants of this node, plus every node has exactly one parent, except for the root node which has no parents.... The given input is a directed graph that started as a rooted tree with n nodes (with distinct values from 1 to n), with one additional directed edge added." So, after adding an edge two things could have happened. 
`Case 1 =>` A child could now have two parents. In which case we will store the two edges to the child. `(candidateA and candidateB)`
`Case 2 =>` The root could now have a parent, which would form a cycle since the root is an ancestor of all nodes.

```
// 1) Check whether there is a node having two parents. If so, store them as candidateA and candidateB. 
// 2) If there is a cycle, perform union-find and return the edge that creates the cycle.
// 3) Else remove candidateA edge and perform union-find. If find of candidateA's parent
// and child are equal return candidateA, otherwise return candidateB 


class Solution {
    int[] parent;

    public int[] findRedundantDirectedConnection(int[][] edges) {
        int n = edges.length;
        parent = new int[n+1];
        int[] candidateA = null;
        int[] candidateB = null;

        for (int[] edge : edges) {
            int parentNode = edge[0];
            int childNode = edge[1];
            if (parent[childNode] == 0) {
                parent[childNode] = parentNode;
            } else {
                candidateA = new int[]{parentNode, childNode};
                candidateB = new int[]{parent[childNode], childNode};
            }
        }

        for (int i = 0; i <= n; i++) {
            parent[i] = i;
        }

        // there must be a cycle, return edge that creates cycle
        if (candidateA == null && candidateB == null) {
            for (int[] edge : edges) {
                int parentNode = edge[0];
                int childNode = edge[1];
                if (!union(parentNode, childNode)) {
                    return edge;
                }
            }
        } else {
            // remove edge candidateA and perform union
            // if find of this removed edge's parent and child are equal
            // return candidateA
            // otherwise return candidateB
            for (int[] edge : edges) {
                int parentNode = edge[0];
                int childNode = edge[1];
                if (candidateA[0] == parentNode && candidateA[1] == childNode) {
                    continue;
                }
                union(parentNode, childNode);
            }
            if (find(candidateA[0]) == find(candidateA[1])) {
                return candidateA;
            } else {
                return candidateB;
            }
        }
        // will never reach here
        return edges[0];
    }

    public int find(int node) {
        int root = node;
        while (root != parent[root]) {
            root = parent[root];
        }

        // path compression
        int curr = node;
        while (curr != root) {
            int next = parent[curr];
            parent[curr] = root;
            curr = next;
        }
        return root;
    }

    public boolean union(int node1, int node2) {
        int root1 = find(node1);
        int root2 = find(node2);
        if (root1 == root2) {
            return false;
        }
        parent[root2] = root1;
        return true;
    }
}
```

