solutions.content:
While connecting an edge to two nodes a->b , we need to check 
i. if a and b are not connected already
ii. if a the parent of b is b, ie b has not been connected with any other node yet
If both condition i and ii are true, then we can connect both of these nodes.

However, if b has already been connected with some other node previously (ie if ii is false), then the two edges
parent[b]->b and a->b are candidate edges. By candidate edges, we mean either of these two need to be removed. We will check later which one needs to be removed. For now, we have already connected the edge parent[b]->b. We will not be considering the edge a->b. 

But if condition i is false, ie, these two nodes have already been connected previously, it means that we have a cycle in our graph, which means that some edge that we had included previously needed to be eliminated. 

Now we know from our candidates, that the edge parent[b]->b was included. So if there is a cycle, exclude this one. If there is no cycle, then the edge a->b stored in candidate, needs to be excluded.



```
class Solution {
public:
    void unionn(vector<int>&parent, int a, int b){
        int p=a;
        int q=b;
        parent[q]=p;
    }
    int root(vector<int>&parent, int a){
        int r=a;
        while(r!=parent[r]){
            r=parent[r];
        }
        return r;
    }
    vector<int> findRedundantDirectedConnection(vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        int n=edges.size();
        vector<int>parent(n+1);

        for(int i=0;i<=n;i++){
            parent[i]=i;
        }
        vector<vector<int> >cand,cycle;
        bool hasCycle=false;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            int a=edges[i][0];
            int b=edges[i][1];
            if(root(parent,a)!=root(parent,b) && parent[b]==b){
                unionn(parent,a,b);
            }else if(parent[b]!=b){
                cand.push_back({parent[b],b});
                cand.push_back({a,b});
            }else{
                hasCycle=true;
                cycle.push_back(edges[i]);
            }
        }
        if(hasCycle){
            if(cand.size()!=0)
                return cand[0];
            return cycle[0];
        }
        return cand[cand.size()-1];
    }
};
```

