solutions.content:
From the question, we know that each node should contain only 1 parent. Therefore we can have 2 cases. 

1. All node contain only 1 parent. Then this is same as last question [Redundant Connection](https://leetcode.com/problems/redundant-connection/discuss/2052496/java-dfs-solution-with-explain). 

	What we need to do is to find out the edge that cause a cycle. 

	Same as in last question, for every edge, we do dfs, if we can start from edge end node (let say v) and find its father, which means adding this edge make a cycle, return this edge. 

2. One node contain 2 parents. Then the redundant edge must be one of the parents edge. 
	a. If there is no cycle, we remove the latter parent edge as the question require us to return edge occurs last.  
	b. If there is cycle, we should remove the first parent edge. Assume we have a node with 2 parents "a", and there is a cycle with "a"
	`a -> b -> c -> a`
	and edge order
	`c -> a, b -> c, a -> b`

	We should remove `a -> b` in normal case, but then "b" contain no parent and "a" still have 2 parents. Our choice is only a's parent, and the redundant one must be the extra parent edge that form the cycle. As we construct the graph according to edge order, the previous parent edge added into graph first before we add the second one, therefore the first one must be the edge in the cycle when we find a cycle. 

```
    public int[] findRedundantDirectedConnection(int[][] edges) {
        int[] parents = new int[edges.length + 1];
        int[] case2a = new int[2];
        int[] case2b = new int[2];

        boolean duplicateParent = false;

        for(int i = 0; i < edges.length; i++){
            int start = edges[i][0];
            int end = edges[i][1];

            if(parents[end] > 0){
                case2a = new int[] {parents[end], end};
                case2b = new int[] {edges[i][0], edges[i][1]};
                duplicateParent = true;
                edges[i][0] = edges[i][1] = -1;
            }else{
                parents[end] = start;
            }
        }

        parents = new int[edges.length + 1];
        for(int i = 0; i < edges.length; i++){
            int start = edges[i][0];
            int end = edges[i][1];
            if(start < 0 || end < 0){
                continue;
            }

            parents[end] = start;

            if(cycle(end, parents)){
                return duplicateParent ? case2a : edges[i];
            }
        }
        return case2b;
    }

    private boolean cycle(int v, int[] parents){
        int parent = parents[v];
        while(parent != 0){
            if(parent == v){
                return true;
            }
            parent = parents[parent];
        }
        return false;
    }
