	The problem states that there is an unnecessary edge which is not letting this graph to be a tree, Now an unncessary edge can lead to the following

		1) It can make a node have two parents
			when only this condition is satisfied, that is there is a node having two parents (and we dont have any cycles),
			simply return the last such edge in the edgeList, this can be done by using an in-degree array, where we store -1
			when no one points to a given node, and in case someone points to this node, we store the location of that node (or the index )
			where it occurred in the edge list
			in the below diagram , the edges in red are causing problem , so remove the one which comes the last in the edge list
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/62eca74a-956c-40e9-8834-ff71a78bec62_1630249079.6178932.png)








		2) It may contain a cycle
			when in the in-degree array, no one has two parents, it means that only way there can exist an unncessary edge is by having a cycle
			so simple detect a cycle using DSU 

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/07d34600-43b6-4431-b301-33fb66f25c6c_1630249205.5177577.png)








		3) both of the above, it may have a node having two parents and a cycle
			In this case when both of the conditions are satisfied, then one of the two parents which point to the node having
			in-degree two is the answer (means parent->node edge)
			In this case, the edge which is contained in the cycle and points to this node having two parents is the answer

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/214979d4-27da-4c26-9aa5-52ee110257c7_1630249285.6398723.png)


