Kruskal Algorithm Solution

1. The first problem we need to solve: when a new edge added , whether the new adding leads to a circle formed in the graph. when a circle is detected, we return the added edge, otherwise, return null;(Kruskal Algorithm), return this result when there is no node has two parents.

2. The problem description gives a limitation that there is only one node in the graph that could have two parent nodes
(e.g. [1,3],[2,3], 3 has two parent nodes 1 and 2), 
which means one of edges must be deleted. First we try delete the last one, and the check the circle existing, if it returns a null, the result should be the deleted edge, otherwise, another edge should be the right answer.
```
class Solution {
    int[] parent1 = new int[2];
    int[] parent2 = new int[2];
    public int[] findRedundantDirectedConnection(int[][] edges) {
        int[] ends = new int[edges.length+1]; 
        ArrayList<int[]> nedges = deleteParent(edges);
        int[] res = checkCircle(nedges,ends);
        if(parent1[0]==0&&parent1[1]==0){
            return res;
        }else{
            if(res != null){
                return parent2;
            }else{
                return parent1;
            }
        }
    }
    //delete one of the edges of the node has two parent node;e.g.[1,3][2,3]
    public  ArrayList<int[]> deleteParent (int[][]edges){
        ArrayList<int[]> nedge = new ArrayList<int[]>();
        HashSet<Integer> tail = new HashSet<Integer>();
        for(int[] e : edges){

            if(!tail.add(e[1])){
                parent1[0]=e[0];
               parent1[1] = e[1];

            }else{
               nedge.add(e); 
            }

        }
        return nedge;
    }

    public int[] checkCircle(ArrayList<int[]>nedges, int[]ends){

        for(int[] edge: nedges){
            if(parent1[1]!=0 && edge[1]== parent1[1]){
                parent2 = edge;
            }
            int h = getEnd(edge[0],ends);
            int t = getEnd(edge[1],ends);
            if(h!=t){
                ends[edge[1]] = h;  
            }else{
                return edge;
            }
        }        
        return null;
    }
    public int getEnd(int head, int[]ends){
        while(ends[head]!= 0){
           head = ends[head];
        }

        return head;
    }
}
