solutions.content:
There are 3 cases in this problem:

1. Every node has ```only one parent```, and there is ```a circle``` which include the root node. That is to say, the root has an enter edge.
2. There is a node with ```two parents```, which have ```one common ancestor``` node.
3. There is a node with ```two parents```, one of which is ```in a circle```.

My solution:
1. Iterator all the edges.
2. For every edge, use ```Union Find``` to find the root of each node. 
3. In the find process, if the node is in a circle, mark it's root to 0.
4. If the roots of the two nodes are the same, it might be the case 1, just mark this edge as ```tempEdge```.
5. If the enter node is not a root one, it must be one has two parents, mark the two edges as ```[u1, v]``` and ```[u2, v]```.
6. After the iteration, if ```[u1, v]``` and ```[u2, v]``` are not exist, just return ```tempEdge```.
7. Else union find u1 and u2, if one of which is in a circle, just return it.
8. Else they must have the common root, just return u2(the last one).


My code:
```java
class Solution {
    public int[] findRedundantDirectedConnection(int[][] edges) {
        int n = edges.length;
        int[] id = new int[n + 1];
        for (int i = 0; i <= n; i++) id[i] = i;

        int[] parents = new int[2];
        int child = 0;
        int[] result = new int[2];
        for (int[] e : edges) {
            int u = e[0], v = e[1];
            int up = find(id, u), vp = find(id, v);

            if (up == vp && child == 0) result = e;
            else if (vp != v) {
                child = v;
                parents[0] = id[v];
                parents[1] = u;
            } else {
                id[v] = u;
            }
        }

        if (child != 0) {
            int root0 = find(id, parents[0]);
            int root1 = find(id, parents[1]);
            if (root0 == root1 || root1 == 0) result = new int[]{parents[1], child};
            else result = new int[]{parents[0], child};
        }

        return result;
    }

    private int find(int[] id, int p) {
        int pp = p;
        while (pp != id[pp]) {
            pp = id[pp];
            if (pp == p) return 0;
        }
        return pp;
    }
