/*
There are basic 3 cases, which divided by two conditions
con 1, there is a circle, con 2 there is a node with two parents.
case 1, there is a circle but no nodes with two parents-- return the first edge complete a circle
case 2, there is a circle, also with a node with two parents -- return the first edge points to the node with two parents
case 3, there is no circle, but with a node with two parents -- return the second edge that points to the node with two parents.

*/
